                =20
<span class=3D"nu0">80</span>/tcp                     ALLOW       Anywhere =
                =20
<span class=3D"nu0">443</span>                        ALLOW       Anywhere =
                =20
<span class=3D"nu0">1022</span>/tcp <span class=3D"br0">(</span>v6<span cla=
ss=3D"br0">)</span>              ALLOW       Anywhere <span class=3D"br0">(=
</span>v6<span class=3D"br0">)</span>              # Open port ssh tcp port=
 <span class=3D"nu0">1022</span> as failsafe option for upgrades
<span class=3D"nu0">22</span>/tcp <span class=3D"br0">(</span>v6<span class=
=3D"br0">)</span>                ALLOW       Anywhere <span class=3D"br0">(=
</span>v6<span class=3D"br0">)</span>            =20
<span class=3D"nu0">80</span>/tcp <span class=3D"br0">(</span>v6<span class=
=3D"br0">)</span>                ALLOW       Anywhere <span class=3D"br0">(=
</span>v6<span class=3D"br0">)</span>            =20
<span class=3D"nu0">443</span> <span class=3D"br0">(</span>v6<span class=3D=
"br0">)</span>                   ALLOW       Anywhere <span class=3D"br0">(=
</span>v6<span class=3D"br0">)</span></pre></div></div></div></div></div></=
div></div>


<h2><a name=3D"Upgrade_to_22.04_LTS_using_the_CLI"></a>Step 4 =E2=80=93 Upg=
rade to 22.04 LTS using the command line <a href=3D"https://www.cyberciti.b=
iz/faq/upgrade-ubuntu-20-04-lts-to-22-04-lts/#TOC" title=3D"Jump back to th=
e table of contents (TOC)" style=3D"text-decoration:none;=20
	font-size: 40px;
margin-left: 7px;
font-weight: bolder;">=E2=86=91</a></h2>
<p>On the command line, type the do-release-upgrade command as follows to s=
tart the update procedure:<br>
<code><span title=3D"The shell prompt usually ends in a $ sign and is not p=
art of the command for the nonprivileged user." class=3D"normaluserprompt">=
$ </span>sudo do-release-upgrade</code></p>
<div class=3D"note">If you do not get updates, try to pass the <kbd>-d</kbd=
>. If using the latest supported release, upgrade to the development releas=
e. For example:<br>
<code><span title=3D"The shell prompt usually ends in a $ sign and is not p=
art of the command for the nonprivileged user." class=3D"normaluserprompt">=
$ </span>sudo do-release-upgrade</code></div>
<p>ssh user will see message immediately:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
ap4"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap3"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlig=
ht-wrap2"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-hig=
hlight"><div class=3D"ini"><pre class=3D"de1">Reading cache
&nbsp;
Checking package manager
&nbsp;
Continue running under SSH?=20
&nbsp;
This session appears to be running under ssh. It is not recommended=20
to perform a upgrade over ssh currently because in case of failure it=20
is harder to recover.=20
&nbsp;
If you continue, an additional ssh daemon will be started at port=20
<span class=3D"st0">'1022'</span>.=20
Do you want to continue?=20
&nbsp;
Continue <span class=3D"re0"><span class=3D"br0">[</span>yN<span class=3D"b=
r0">]</span></span> y</pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>


<p>Type =E2=80=98y=E2=80=99 and then you will get another message:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
ap4"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap3"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlig=
ht-wrap2"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-hig=
hlight"><div class=3D"ini"><pre class=3D"de1">Starting additional sshd=20
&nbsp;
To make recovery in case of failure easier, an additional sshd will=20
be started on port <span class=3D"st0">'1022'</span>. If anything goes wron=
g with the running=20
ssh you can still connect to the additional one.=20
If you run a firewall, you may need to temporarily open this port. As=20
this is potentially dangerous it<span class=3D"st0">'s not done automatical=
ly. You can=20
open the port with e.g.:=20
'</span>iptables -I INPUT -p tcp --dport <span class=3D"nu0">1022</span> -j=
 ACCEPT<span class=3D"st0">'=20
&nbsp;
To continue please press [ENTER]</span></pre></div></div></div></div></div>=
</div></div>


<p>Since we already opened port 1022, press the <kbd>[Enter]</kbd> key to c=
ontinue. Then you need to confirm focal to jammy update entries:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
ap4"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap3"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlig=
ht-wrap2"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-hig=
hlight"><div class=3D"ini"><pre class=3D"de1">Do you want to rewrite your <=
span class=3D"st0">'sources.list'</span> file anyway? If you choose=20
<span class=3D"st0">'Yes'</span> here it will update all <span class=3D"st0=
">'focal'</span> to <span class=3D"st0">'jammy'</span> entries.=20
If you select <span class=3D"st0">'No'</span> the upgrade will cancel.=20
&nbsp;
Continue <span class=3D"re0"><span class=3D"br0">[</span>yN<span class=3D"b=
r0">]</span></span> y</pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>


<h3>Confirming upgrade procedure</h3>
<p>Again you will get final prompt with details as follows:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
ap4"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap3"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlig=
ht-wrap2"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-hig=
hlight"><div class=3D"ini"><pre class=3D"de1">Do you want to start the upgr=
ade?=20
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<span class=3D"nu0">14</span> installed packages are no longer supported by=
 Canonical. You can=20
still get support from the community.=20
&nbsp;
<span class=3D"nu0">5</span> packages are going to be removed. <span class=
=3D"nu0">90</span> new packages are going to be=20
installed. <span class=3D"nu0">570</span> packages are going to be upgraded=
.=20
&nbsp;
You have to download a total of <span class=3D"nu0">546</span> M. This down=
load will take about=20
<span class=3D"nu0">1</span> minute with a 40Mbit connection and about <spa=
n class=3D"nu0">14</span> minutes with a 5Mbit=20
connection.=20
&nbsp;
Fetching and installing the upgrade can take several hours. Once the=20
download has finished, the process cannot be canceled.=20
&nbsp;
 Continue <span class=3D"re0"><span class=3D"br0">[</span>yN<span class=3D"=
br0">]</span>  Details <span class=3D"br0">[</span>d<span class=3D"br0">]</=
span></span> y</pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>


<p>Finally hit the <kbd>ENTER</kbd> again:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
ap4"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap3"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlig=
