 the lock screen be disabled during the=20
upgrade to prevent later issues. Please ensure your screen lock is=20
disabled before continuing.=20
&nbsp;
To continue please press <span class=3D"re0"><span class=3D"br0">[</span>EN=
TER<span class=3D"br0">]</span></span></pre></div></div></div></div></div><=
/div></div>


<p>Also make sure you confirm to restart services when asked. For example, =
do you want to keep your existing sshd config file?<br>
<img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://www.cyberciti.biz/m=
edia/new/faq/2022/04/Keep-sshd-config-on-Ubuntu-Linux-20.04-LTS-when-upgrad=
ing-to-22.04-LTS-599x304.png" alt=3D"Keep sshd config on Ubuntu Linux 20.04=
 LTS when upgrading to 22.04 LTS" width=3D"599" height=3D"304" class=3D"ali=
gncenter size-medium wp-image-150380"></p>
<h3>Dealing with obsolete package on Ubuntu</h3>
<p>You may be prompted to remove obsolete package as follows:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
