er confirm it by pressing the <kbd>y</kbd> or deny it by pressing the <kbd>=
N</kbd></p>
<h3>System upgrade is complete</h3>
<p>After some time, you will get confirmation on the screen. A restart is r=
equired to finish the upgrade from 20.04 LTS to 22.04. Make sure you choose=
 <kbd>y</kbd>, and then Ubuntu will restart:<br>
<img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://www.cyberciti.biz/m=
edia/new/faq/2022/04/How-to-upgrade-from-Ubuntu-20.04-LTS-to-22.04-LTS-599x=
276.png" alt=3D"How to upgrade from Ubuntu 20.04 LTS to 22.04 LTS" width=3D=
"599" height=3D"276" class=3D"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-150381"></p>
<div class=3D"note">Do not forget to <a href=3D"https://www.cyberciti.biz/f=
aq/how-to-delete-a-ufw-firewall-rule-on-ubuntu-debian-linux/" title=3D"How =
to delete a UFW firewall rule on Ubuntu / Debian Linux">delete ufw rule tha=
t you used to open tcp/1022</a>. For example:<br>
<code><span title=3D"The shell prompt usually ends in a $ sign and is not p=
art of the command for the nonprivileged user." class=3D"normaluserprompt">=
$ </span>ufw delete allow 1022/tcp</code><br>
<span style=3D"color: #999999;">Outputs:</span><p></p>


