ht-wrap2"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-hig=
hlight"><div class=3D"ini"><pre class=3D"de1">Rule deleted
Rule deleted <span class=3D"br0">(</span>v6<span class=3D"br0">)</span></pr=
e></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>


</div>
<h2><a name=3D"Verification"></a>Step 5 =E2=80=93 Verification <a href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/upgrade-ubuntu-20-04-lts-to-22-04-lts/#TOC" ti=
tle=3D"Jump back to the table of contents (TOC)" style=3D"text-decoration:n=
one;=20
	font-size: 40px;
margin-left: 7px;
font-weight: bolder;">=E2=86=91</a></h2>
<p>Once the system is restarted, you can log in using GUI or ssh based sess=
ion. Then you can <a href=3D"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/find-print-linux=
-unix-kernel-version/" title=3D"How To Find Which Linux Kernel Version Is I=
nstalled On My System">view the Linux kernel version</a>, run:<br>
<code><span title=3D"The shell prompt usually ends in a $ sign and is not p=
art of the command for the nonprivileged user." class=3D"normaluserprompt">=
$ </span>uname -mrs</code><br>
<span style=3D"color: #999999;">Outputs:</span></p>
<pre>Linux 5.15.0-25-generic x86_64</pre>
<p>Of course, use the lsb_release command too:<br>
<code><span title=3D"The shell prompt usually ends in a $ sign and is not p=
art of the command for the nonprivileged user." class=3D"normaluserprompt">=
$ </span>lsb_release -a</code><br>
<span style=3D"color: #999999;">Sample outputs:</span></p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
ap4"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap3"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlig=
ht-wrap2"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-hig=
hlight"><div class=3D"ini"><pre class=3D"de1">No LSB modules are available.
Distributor ID:	Ubuntu
Description:	Ubuntu Jammy Jellyfish <span class=3D"br0">(</span>development=
 branch<span class=3D"br0">)</span>
Release:	<span class=3D"nu0">22.04</span>
Codename:	jammy</pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>


<h2><a name=3D"Enable_3rd_party_repos/mirros"></a>Step 6 =E2=80=93 Enable 3=
rd party repos/mirros <a href=3D"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/upgrade-ubun=
tu-20-04-lts-to-22-04-lts/#TOC" title=3D"Jump back to the table of contents=
 (TOC)" style=3D"text-decoration:none;=20
	font-size: 40px;
margin-left: 7px;
font-weight: bolder;">=E2=86=91</a></h2>
<p>Now that Ubuntu 20.04 LTS to 22.04 LTS upgrade is completed, make sure 3=
rd party mirror and repos are enabled. Otherwise, you will not get updates.=
 Use the <a href=3D"https://bash.cyberciti.biz/guide/Cd_command" title=3D"C=
d command - Linux Bash Shell Scripting Tutorial Wiki">cd command</a> as fol=
lows:<br>
<code><span title=3D"The shell prompt usually ends in a $ sign and is not p=
art of the command for the nonprivileged user." class=3D"normaluserprompt">=
$ </span>cd /etc/apt/sources.list.d<br>
<span title=3D"The shell prompt usually ends in a $ sign and is not part of=
 the command for the nonprivileged user." class=3D"normaluserprompt">$ </sp=
an>ls -l</code><br>
For example, my app repo was disabled during updates:<br>
<code><span title=3D"The shell prompt usually ends in a $ sign and is not p=
art of the command for the nonprivileged user." class=3D"normaluserprompt">=
$ </span>cat my-apps.list</code><br>
<span style=3D"color: #999999;">Outputs:</span></p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
ap4"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap3"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlig=
ht-wrap2"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-hig=
hlight"><div class=3D"ini"><pre class=3D"de1">#deb <span class=3D"re0"><spa=
n class=3D"br0">[</span>arch<span class=3D"sy0">=3D</span><span class=3D"re=
2">amd64<span class=3D"br0">]</span></span> https://dl.lan.cyberciti.biz/li=
nux/deb/ stable main</span></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>


<p>To enable it again, I commented out the line by removing the <kbd>#</kbd=
>:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wrap5"><div class=3D"wp-geshi-highlight-wr=
