						</div>
						<div class=3D"comment_text" id=3D"comment-body-943434">
<p>A few extra recommendations:</p>
<p>1. Snap packages if installed will try to reinstall themselves after all=
 upgrade deb packages were downloaded and main upgrade process is started. =
Thus if one of them fails to download or update whole process will be rolle=
d back. Which is not always clean and recoverable operation. You may want t=
o turn snap updates off before upgrade or temporarily remove snap packages,=
 especially when on not very fast and stable internet connection.</p>
<p>2. NVidia graphics users may experience driver update failures during up=
grade. In my case nvidia-390 failed to install because of old broken depend=
encies. Not a critical issue but may frighten well an inexperienced user. L=
ooks like system hangs up completely after reboot and almost as if upgrade =
totally failed and all is lost. But in fact it will be just a driver failur=
e that is cured by entering recovery console and the driver fix (sometimes =
a tricky matter). So my advise would be to switch to native xserver nouveau=
 drivers before upgrade and reinstall proprietary nvidia driver after succe=
ssful boot. Which, I guess, Nvidia users should know well how to do.</p>
						</div>
