<p>Thanks for your guide it was helpful.  I did have an issue on reboot tha=
t I had to research a solution.  I had a USB drive being mounted in my fsta=
b which was no longer connected.  20.04 would just try to mount it and move=
 along and boot normally.  22.04 stopped and left me in emergency mode to b=
e able to check logs, etc, to see what it was not booting.  I searched the =
error message and saw that someone else just did a =E2=80=9Cmount -a=E2=80=
=9D which showed the drive that was not mounting.  I then found that drive =
in my fstab and commented out that line.  I was then able to be normally.</=
p>
